{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1115,"text":"So a chip, a poet and a boy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":6520,"text":"It's just about 20 years ago,"},{"time":8485,"text":"June 1994, when Intel announced"},{"time":11989,"text":"that there was a flaw"},{"time":14002,"text":"at the core of their Pentium chip."},{"time":16819,"text":"Deep in the code of the SRT algorithm"},{"time":19200,"text":"to calculate intermediate quotients necessary"},{"time":21451,"text":"for iterative floating points of divisions --"},{"time":23285,"text":"I don't know what that means, but \nit's what it says on Wikipedia —"},{"time":26384,"text":"there was a flaw and an error"},{"time":29263,"text":"that meant that there was a certain probability"},{"time":31479,"text":"that the result of the calculation would be an error,"},{"time":34487,"text":"and the probability was one out of every"},{"time":37080,"text":"360 billion calculations."},{"time":40617,"text":"So Intel said your average spreadsheet"},{"time":42611,"text":"would be flawed once every 27,000 years."},{"time":47117,"text":"They didn't think it was significant,"},{"time":48411,"text":"but there was an outrage in the community."},{"time":51637,"text":"The community, the techies, said, this flaw"},{"time":53987,"text":"has to be addressed."},{"time":55068,"text":"They were not going to stand by quietly"},{"time":57069,"text":"as Intel gave them these chips."},{"time":59017,"text":"So there was a revolution across the world."},{"time":61063,"text":"People marched to demand --"},{"time":64093,"text":"okay, not really exactly like that —"},{"time":66202,"text":"but they rose up and they demanded"},{"time":68943,"text":"that Intel fix the flaw."},{"time":71935,"text":"And Intel set aside 475 million dollars"},{"time":77787,"text":"to fund the replacement of millions of chips"},{"time":80029,"text":"to fix the flaw."},{"time":81120,"text":"So billions of dollars in our society"},{"time":83332,"text":"was spent to address a problem"},{"time":85516,"text":"which would come once out of every 360 billion"},{"time":89607,"text":"calculations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91694,"text":"Number two, a poet."},{"time":94297,"text":"This is Martin Niemöller."},{"time":96577,"text":"You're familiar with his poetry."},{"time":98110,"text":"Around the height of the Nazi period,"},{"time":99886,"text":"he started repeating the verse,"},{"time":102158,"text":"\"First they came for the communists,"},{"time":103893,"text":"and I did nothing,"},{"time":105424,"text":"did not speak out because I was not a communist."},{"time":107674,"text":"Then they came for the socialists."},{"time":108728,"text":"Then they came for the trade unions."},{"time":110690,"text":"Then they came for the Jews."},{"time":111936,"text":"And then they came for me."},{"time":114838,"text":"But there was no one left to speak for me.\""},{"time":119509,"text":"Now, Niemöller is offering a certain kind of insight."},{"time":122638,"text":"This is an insight at the core of intelligence."},{"time":125970,"text":"We could call it cluefulness."},{"time":128684,"text":"It's a certain kind of test:"},{"time":131245,"text":"Can you recognize"},{"time":133037,"text":"an underlying threat and respond?"},{"time":135541,"text":"Can you save yourself or save your kind?"},{"time":139031,"text":"Turns out ants are pretty good at this."},{"time":140770,"text":"Cows, not so much."},{"time":142853,"text":"So can you see the pattern?"},{"time":145283,"text":"Can you see a pattern and then recognize"},{"time":147630,"text":"and do something about it? Number two."},{"time":151682,"text":"Number three, a boy."},{"time":153609,"text":"This is my friend Aaron Swartz."},{"time":155910,"text":"He's Tim's friend."},{"time":157341,"text":"He's friends of many of you in this audience,"},{"time":159373,"text":"and seven years ago,"},{"time":160798,"text":"Aaron came to me with a question."},{"time":163784,"text":"It was just before I was going\nto give my first TED Talk."},{"time":166367,"text":"I was so proud. I was telling him about my talk,"},{"time":168790,"text":"\"Laws that choke creativity.\""},{"time":171297,"text":"And Aaron looked at me"},{"time":172906,"text":"and was a little impatient, and he said,"},{"time":174857,"text":"\"So how are you ever"},{"time":178950,"text":"going to solve the problems you're talking about?"},{"time":180990,"text":"Copyright policy, Internet policy,"},{"time":182792,"text":"how are you ever going to address those problems"},{"time":185982,"text":"so long as there's this fundamental corruption"},{"time":189215,"text":"in the way our government works?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":192060,"text":"So I was a little put off by this."},{"time":194665,"text":"He wasn't sharing in my celebration."},{"time":196650,"text":"And I said to him, \"You know, Aaron,"},{"time":197817,"text":"it's not my field, not my field.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":200911,"text":"He said, \"You mean as an\nacademic, it's not your field?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":203467,"text":"I said, \"Yeah, as an academic, it's not my field.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":206061,"text":"He said, \"What about as a citizen?"},{"time":209392,"text":"As a citizen.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":212819,"text":"Now, this is the way Aaron was."},{"time":214415,"text":"He didn't tell. He asked questions."},{"time":219476,"text":"But his questions spoke as clearly"},{"time":221226,"text":"as my four-year-old's hug."},{"time":223914,"text":"He was saying to me,"},{"time":225330,"text":"\"You've got to get a clue."},{"time":227262,"text":"You have got to get a clue, because there is"},{"time":228938,"text":"a flaw at the core of the operating system"},{"time":232000,"text":"of this democracy,"},{"time":233507,"text":"and it's not a flaw every one out of 360 billion times"},{"time":237805,"text":"our democracy tries to make a decision."},{"time":239597,"text":"It is every time,"},{"time":241418,"text":"every single important issue."},{"time":243814,"text":"We've got to end the bovinity of this political society."},{"time":248347,"text":"We've got to adopt, it turns out,"},{"time":249990,"text":"the word is fourmi-formatic attitude --"},{"time":252762,"text":"that's what the Internet tells me the word is --"},{"time":254532,"text":"the ant's appreciative attitude"},{"time":256604,"text":"that gets us to recognize this flaw,"},{"time":259242,"text":"save our kind and save our demos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265055,"text":"Now if you know Aaron Swartz,"},{"time":266533,"text":"you know that we lost him"},{"time":270171,"text":"just over a year ago."},{"time":272503,"text":"It was about six weeks"},{"time":274039,"text":"before I gave my TED Talk,"},{"time":275919,"text":"and I was so grateful to Chris"},{"time":277814,"text":"that he asked me to give this TED Talk,"},{"time":279245,"text":"not because I had the chance to talk to you,"},{"time":281445,"text":"although that was great,"},{"time":283729,"text":"but because it pulled me out\nof an extraordinary depression."},{"time":287162,"text":"I couldn't begin to describe the sadness."},{"time":291671,"text":"Because I had to focus."},{"time":292951,"text":"I had to focus on, what was I going to say to you?"},{"time":297266,"text":"It saved me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299468,"text":"But after the buzz, the excitement,"},{"time":301417,"text":"the power that comes from this community,"},{"time":305892,"text":"I began to yearn for a less sterile,"},{"time":308443,"text":"less academic way to address these issues,"},{"time":310960,"text":"the issues that I was talking about."},{"time":314749,"text":"We'd begun to focus on New Hampshire"},{"time":316605,"text":"as a target for this political movement,"},{"time":319273,"text":"because the primary in New Hampshire"},{"time":321810,"text":"is so incredibly important."},{"time":323600,"text":"It was a group called the New Hampshire Rebellion"},{"time":326201,"text":"that was beginning to talk about, how would we make"},{"time":328519,"text":"this issue of this corruption central in 2016?"},{"time":331769,"text":"But it was another soul that caught my imagination,"},{"time":335210,"text":"a woman named Doris Haddock, aka Granny D."},{"time":340547,"text":"On January 1, 1999, 15 years ago,"},{"time":343909,"text":"at the age of 88, Granny D started a walk."},{"time":348738,"text":"She started in Los Angeles"},{"time":352008,"text":"and began to walk to Washington, D.C."},{"time":354970,"text":"with a single sign on her chest that said,"},{"time":357698,"text":"\"campaign finance reform.\""},{"time":360282,"text":"Eighteen months later,"},{"time":363010,"text":"at the age of 90,"},{"time":364820,"text":"she arrived in Washington\nwith hundreds following her,"},{"time":367346,"text":"including many congressmen\nwho had gotten in a car"},{"time":369664,"text":"and driven out about a mile outside of the city"},{"time":372572,"text":"to walk in with her."},{"time":374460,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":376602,"text":"Now, I don't have 13 months"},{"time":379892,"text":"to walk across the country."},{"time":381534,"text":"I've got three kids who hate to walk,"},{"time":384176,"text":"and a wife who, it turns out,"},{"time":385578,"text":"still hates when I'm not there"},{"time":387476,"text":"for mysterious reasons,"},{"time":388645,"text":"so this was not an option,"},{"time":389950,"text":"but the question I asked,"},{"time":391110,"text":"could we remix Granny D a bit?"},{"time":393658,"text":"What about a walk not of 3,200 miles"},{"time":395790,"text":"but of 185 miles across New Hampshire"},{"time":399710,"text":"in January?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":403314,"text":"So on January 11,"},{"time":405540,"text":"the anniversary of Aaron's death,"},{"time":408426,"text":"we began a walk that ended on January 24th,"},{"time":412169,"text":"the day that Granny D was born."},{"time":416515,"text":"A total of 200 people joined us across this walk,"},{"time":421095,"text":"as we went from the very top to the\nvery bottom of New Hampshire"},{"time":424869,"text":"talking about this issue."},{"time":427265,"text":"And what was astonishing to me,"},{"time":428865,"text":"something I completely did not expect to find,"},{"time":431426,"text":"was the passion and anger"},{"time":434021,"text":"that there was among everyone\nthat we talked to about this issue."},{"time":439496,"text":"We had found in a poll that 96 percent of Americans"},{"time":444602,"text":"believe it important to reduce the influence"},{"time":446441,"text":"of money in politics."},{"time":448687,"text":"Now politicians and pundits tell you,"},{"time":450703,"text":"there's nothing we can do about this issue,"},{"time":452523,"text":"Americans don't care about it,"},{"time":453859,"text":"but the reason for that is"},{"time":456155,"text":"that 91 percent of Americans"},{"time":458009,"text":"think there's nothing that can\nbe done about this issue."},{"time":462531,"text":"And it's this gap between 96 and 91"},{"time":465353,"text":"that explains our politics of resignation."},{"time":467830,"text":"I mean, after all, at least 96 percent of us"},{"time":469913,"text":"wish we could fly like Superman,"},{"time":471775,"text":"but because at least 91 percent\nof us believe we can't,"},{"time":474939,"text":"we don't leap off of tall buildings every time"},{"time":477605,"text":"we have that urge."},{"time":478915,"text":"That's because we accept our limits,"},{"time":480921,"text":"and so too with this reform."},{"time":483680,"text":"But when you give people the sense of hope,"},{"time":487973,"text":"you begin to thaw that\nabsolute sense of impossibility."},{"time":494690,"text":"As Harvey Milk said, if you give 'em hope,"},{"time":498305,"text":"you give 'em a chance, a way to think"},{"time":501020,"text":"about how this change is possible."},{"time":503109,"text":"Hope."},{"time":505960,"text":"And hope is the one thing that we, Aaron's friends,"},{"time":509530,"text":"failed him with, because we let him"},{"time":512527,"text":"lose that sense of hope."},{"time":518127,"text":"I loved that boy like I love my son."},{"time":526233,"text":"But we failed him."},{"time":530202,"text":"And I love my country,"},{"time":533790,"text":"and I'm not going to fail that."},{"time":536144,"text":"I'm not going to fail that."},{"time":537316,"text":"That sense of hope, we're going to hold,"},{"time":541009,"text":"and we're going to fight for,"},{"time":542475,"text":"however impossible this battle looks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":547175,"text":"What's next?"},{"time":548469,"text":"Well, we started with this march with 200 people,"},{"time":551630,"text":"and next year, there will be 1,000"},{"time":555032,"text":"on different routes"},{"time":556671,"text":"that march in the month of January"},{"time":559181,"text":"and meet in Concord to celebrate this cause,"},{"time":563009,"text":"and then in 2016, before the primary,"},{"time":565569,"text":"there will be 10,000 who march across that state,"},{"time":568530,"text":"meeting in Concord to celebrate this cause."},{"time":571594,"text":"And as we have marched, people around the country"},{"time":574365,"text":"have begun to say, \"Can we do the same thing"},{"time":576223,"text":"in our state?\""},{"time":577340,"text":"So we've started a platform called G.D. Walkers,"},{"time":579719,"text":"that is, Granny D walkers,"},{"time":581710,"text":"and Granny D walkers across the country"},{"time":583837,"text":"will be marching for this reform. Number one."},{"time":586939,"text":"Number two, on this march,"},{"time":589219,"text":"one of the founders of Thunderclap, David Cascino,"},{"time":592011,"text":"was with us,"},{"time":593630,"text":"and he said, \"Well what can we do?\""},{"time":595488,"text":"And so they developed a platform,"},{"time":597817,"text":"which we are announcing today,"},{"time":599739,"text":"that allows us to pull together voters"},{"time":602205,"text":"who are committed to this idea of reform."},{"time":604883,"text":"Regardless of where you are,"},{"time":606029,"text":"in New Hampshire or outside of New Hampshire,"},{"time":608681,"text":"you can sign up and directly be informed"},{"time":610591,"text":"where the candidates are on this issue"},{"time":613579,"text":"so you can decide who to vote for"},{"time":615219,"text":"as a function of which is going"},{"time":618137,"text":"to make this possibility real."},{"time":622605,"text":"And then finally number three, the hardest."},{"time":626677,"text":"We're in the age of the Super PAC."},{"time":628500,"text":"Indeed yesterday, Merriam announced"},{"time":630609,"text":"that Merriam-Webster will have Super PAC as a word."},{"time":634859,"text":"It is now an official word in the dictionary."},{"time":638499,"text":"So on May 1, aka May Day,"},{"time":643894,"text":"we're going to try an experiment."},{"time":646681,"text":"We're going to try a launching"},{"time":648498,"text":"of what we can think of as a Super PAC"},{"time":650796,"text":"to end all Super PACs."},{"time":654060,"text":"And the basic way this works is this."},{"time":655860,"text":"For the last year, we have been working"},{"time":657632,"text":"with analysts and political experts"},{"time":661352,"text":"to calculate, how much would it cost"},{"time":664684,"text":"to win enough votes in the United States Congress"},{"time":667106,"text":"to make fundamental reform possible?"},{"time":668926,"text":"What is that number? Half a billion? A billion?"},{"time":671728,"text":"What is that number?"},{"time":673568,"text":"And then whatever that number is,"},{"time":676333,"text":"we are going to kickstart, sort of,"},{"time":678438,"text":"because you can't use KickStarter for political work,"},{"time":680369,"text":"but anyway, kickstart, sort of,"},{"time":683140,"text":"first a bottom-up campaign"},{"time":685496,"text":"where people will make small dollar commitments"},{"time":688476,"text":"contingent on reaching very ambitious goals,"},{"time":691438,"text":"and when those goals have been reached,"},{"time":693438,"text":"we will turn to the large dollar contributors,"},{"time":697577,"text":"to get them to contribute to make it possible"},{"time":700959,"text":"for us to run the kind of Super PAC necessary"},{"time":704482,"text":"to win this issue,"},{"time":705824,"text":"to change the way money influences politics,"},{"time":708718,"text":"so that on November 8,"},{"time":712489,"text":"which I discovered yesterday is the day"},{"time":714817,"text":"that Aaron would have been 30 years old,"},{"time":718508,"text":"on November 8,"},{"time":721200,"text":"we will celebrate 218 representatives"},{"time":724739,"text":"in the House and 60 Senators"},{"time":726826,"text":"in the United States Senate"},{"time":728847,"text":"who have committed to this idea"},{"time":731140,"text":"of fundamental reform."}]},{"cues":[{"time":733006,"text":"So last night, we heard about wishes."},{"time":736768,"text":"Here's my wish."},{"time":738856,"text":"May one."},{"time":742100,"text":"May the ideals of one boy"},{"time":745483,"text":"unite one nation behind one critical idea"},{"time":749964,"text":"that we are one people,"},{"time":752425,"text":"we are the people who were promised a government,"},{"time":755902,"text":"a government that was promised to be"},{"time":758031,"text":"dependent upon the people alone, the people,"},{"time":762752,"text":"who, as Madison told us,"},{"time":765601,"text":"meant not the rich more than the poor."},{"time":769178,"text":"May one."},{"time":771324,"text":"And then may you, may you join this movement,"},{"time":775503,"text":"not because you're a politician,"},{"time":777511,"text":"not because you're an expert,"},{"time":779127,"text":"not because this is your field,"},{"time":782419,"text":"but because if you are,"},{"time":784099,"text":"you are a citizen."},{"time":787770,"text":"Aaron asked me that."},{"time":790807,"text":"Now I've asked you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":793662,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":795340,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}